AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000063 "A simulation of an organism in a simulated population that has participated in an epidemic control measure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000600 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000063 "A simulated organism in a simulated population has participated in a particular simulated control measure. (e.g. an organism received antiviral treatment)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:APOLLO_SV_00000063 "simulation of control measure participant"@en)
EquivalentClasses(obo:APOLLO_SV_00000063 ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:APOLLO_SV_00000067 ObjectIntersectionOf(obo:OBI_0100026 ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000056 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000029))) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(obo:RO_0000056 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000005)))
SubClassOf(obo:APOLLO_SV_00000063 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000034)

# Class: obo:APOLLO_SV_00000064 (simulation time series)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000064 "A time sampled measurement data set, where the position in the sequence of each data item corresponds to a specific time_step of the simulation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000600 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000064 "A sequence of data points, where the position in the sequence of each data point corresponds to a specific time_step of the simulation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment obo:APOLLO_SV_00000064 "MB: The ontological status of simulations (Thoughts)

One property that seems to be common among simulations in comparison to many other fictions is the fact that the chronological order of the simulated purely intentional entities is not changed in the process of simulating.

While in many pieces of fiction the order in which the purely intentional entities are created can vary, this is not the case for simulations."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:APOLLO_SV_00000064 "simulation time series"@en)
SubClassOf(obo:APOLLO_SV_00000064 obo:IAO_0000584)

