# Class: obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 (resistance to infection)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 "The dispostion of an organism of a particular biological taxon A that is realized by inhibiting the establishment of an infection by an organism of another particular biological taxon that bears an infectious disposition towards members of A"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000117 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 "Mathias Brochhausen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000117 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 "William R. Hogan"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000232 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 "Key issue with equivalent class axiom is how to say that this scattered molecular aggregate is both 1) not originally part of the organism and/or 2) is temporary.

I suppose baby could be born with drug acquired from its mother's system.

Somehow, it's not innate and it's temporary, ie, the body will eventually clear it."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000600 obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 "The dispostion of an organism of a particular biological taxon A that is realized by inhibiting the establishment of an infection by an organism of another particular biological taxon that bears an infectious disposition towards members of A"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 "resistance to infection"@en)
SubClassOf(obo:APOLLO_SV_00000145 obo:BFO_0000016)

