# Class: obo:BFO_0000182 (history)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000600 obo:BFO_0000182 "A history is a process that is the sum of the totality of processes taking place in the spatiotemporal region occupied by a material entity or site, including processes on the surface of the entity or within the cavities to which it serves as host. "@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:BFO_0000182 "history"@en)

