# Class: obo:DOID_12205 (dengue disease)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:DOID_12205 "A viral infectious disease that results_in infection, has_material_basis_in Dengue virus [NCBITaxon:12637] with four serotypes (Dengue virus 1, 2, 3 and 4), which are transmitted_by Aedes mosquito bite. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom severe headache, has_symptom severe pain behind the eyes, has_symptom joint pain, has_symptom muscle and bone pain, has_symptom rash, and has_symptom mild bleeding.")
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000412 obo:DOID_12205 "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/doid.owl")
