# Class: obo:DOID_12206 (dengue hemorrhagic fever)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:DOID_12206 "A dengue disease that occurs when a person experiences a second infection with a heterologous Dengue virus serotype, which is transmitted_by Aedes mosquito bite. The infection has_symptom hemorrhagic lesions of the skin, has_symptom thrombocytopenia, has_symptom reduction in the fluid part of the blood, and has_symptom high fever.")
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000412 obo:DOID_12206 "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/doid.owl")
