# Class: obo:ENVO_01000703 (hydrological precipitation process)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:ENVO_01000703 "Hydrological precipitation is a process during which any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour is pulled to the planetary surface by gravity.")
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000412 obo:ENVO_01000703 "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo.owl")
AnnotationAssertion(oboInOwl:hasBroadSynonym obo:ENVO_01000703 "precipitation")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment obo:ENVO_01000703 "\"process\" is included in the label to make it clear that we are not referring to the precipitated material (e.g. snow, rain, sleet)")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label obo:ENVO_01000703 "hydrological precipitation process"@en)
SubClassOf(obo:ENVO_01000703 obo:ENVO_02500000)

