# Class: obo:OAE_0000055 (contraindication)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:OAE_0000055 "A contraindication is a disposition that increases the risk of harm involved in using a particular drug, carrying out a medical procedure, or engaging in a particular activity such that the risk of harm exceeds a threshold. An contraindication serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical treatment."@en)
